# Spotify API Credentials
#
# To get your credentials:
# 1. Go to https://developer.spotify.com/dashboard
# 2. Log in with your Spotify account
# 3. Click "Create app"
# 4. Fill in app details:
#    - App name: Any name you want
#    - App description: Any description
#    - Redirect URI: http://127.0.0.1:3000/callback
# 5. Click "Settings" to view your Client ID and Client Secret
#
# Note: The script uses OAuth 2.0 Authorization Code Flow.
# On first run, it will open a browser for authorization and cache the token.

SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret_here

# Genius API Credentials (for lyrics fetching)
#
# To get your credentials:
# 1. Go to https://genius.com/api-clients
# 2. Click "New API Client"
# 3. Fill in app details:
#    - App name: Any name you want
#    - App Website URL: http://localhost
#    - Redirect URI: http://localhost
# 4. Generate "Client Access Token" (NOT Client ID/Secret)
# 5. Copy the access token and paste below
#
GENIUS_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_genius_access_token_here
